lenders.name: A+ Team Impact Fund at Foundation Beyond Belief
lenders.loan_because: We are the A+ Team Impact Fund at Foundation Beyond Belief (FBB). The A+ Team is the Kiva lending team Atheists, Agnostics, Skeptics, Freethinkers, Secular Humanists, and the Non-Religious. Our mission is to advance the fundamental principle of doing good without relying on a god, and to empower people around the world in attaining the capital and tools they need to meet their own goals. Our purpose is to motivate concerned citizens of the world to support the Fund, to distribute microloans to people living in poverty, and to achieve maximum impact for the donor’s dollar. Our vision is to advance entrepreneurship and to alleviate global poverty and suffering. The A+ Team Impact Fund at FBB will attribute 100% of its loans to the Kiva A + Team.
lenders.occupational_info: FBB is a 501(c)(3) organization that has joined forces with the A+ Team at Kiva to create a microlending fund that makes Kiva loans and attributes those loans to the A+ Team, in perpetuity. The Impact Fund at FBB is the fruit of this collaboration. We emphasize supporting loans that are SECULAR, SAFE, AND SHORT-TERM. Funds donated to the Impact Fund will be distributed quarterly to a “locked” FBB-controlled and -supported Kiva lending account. We rely on donations to get the funds that we lend. Please consider making a donation to support our efforts. Donations to the Impact Fund may be tax-deductible for U.S. taxpayers who itemize their deductions. (Consult your tax adviser for specifics.) If no receipt for a tax deduction is needed, a Kiva Card can be given to the Impact Fund. Send a Private Message to Captain Craig of the A+ Team with the Kiva Card code and amount. Checks from employers for matching contributions, from Donor-Advised Funds, and from IRA custodians should be sent to: Foundation Beyond Belief, 4575 Webb Bridge Road #5992, Alpharetta, GA 30005. Telephone: 770-667-6347. The check should be made payable to “Foundation Beyond Belief A+ Team Impact Fund.” The Employer Identification Number (EIN) of FBB is 26-4822541. To learn more about the Impact Fund, our lending policies, or to make a tax-deductible donation, please visit our website below. Thank you for your support.
